The camera dollies sideways, keeping her face in frame as she looks up at the branches closing above, then back into the camera with a piercing stare.

The camera pushes in toward her glassy eyes as she looks back up from the distortion, her stare sharp and unblinking.

The lens arcs around her upper body, each angle catching distorted versions of her face in the reflections, her real eyes locked on the lens.

A pale-skinned woman kneels by violet water, cupping her hands as glowing droplets fall upward from her palms into the sky. The camera tilts gently down to her hands, then rises back to her face as she glances around at the unnatural silence before fixing her gaze on the lens.

A pale-skinned woman walks slowly through glowing mist, reaching out as ghostly whisper-like shapes swirl around her fingers. The camera tracks alongside her in profile, then eases forward to her face as she turns and watches the whispers drift past.

A pale-skinned woman stands in waist-deep glowing water, lifting both arms as luminous ribbons of whisper-like light swirl into her chest with each breath. The camera tilts up from her arms to her face as she closes her eyes, then opens them suddenly toward the lens.

A pale-skinned woman leans forward, cupping glittering dust from the air in her hands before bringing it to her lips. The camera pushes closer as she exhales, silver glitter spilling heavily from her mouth into the water below, her eyes shimmering as she looks into the camera.

A pale-skinned woman walks across a dark void of stars, her silver hair dissolving into black smoke with each step. The camera tracks backward as she approaches, her hand brushing through the smoke as if testing whether it’s real, before her eyes rise to meet the lens.

A pale-skinned woman leans over a black pool, reaching down to touch her reflection. The shadowed double reaches back from the water, moving differently than her. The camera arcs slowly as she lifts her face, torn between the reflection and the camera’s gaze.

A pale-skinned woman lifts her hand to her cheek, crystalline tears falling upward into her palm. She opens her hand, letting them float away into the starry night. The camera circles gently around her upper body as she watches them vanish, her eyes shining before she returns her gaze to the lens.

A pale-skinned woman drifts backward in violet water, her arms spreading slowly as glowing shards shaped like frozen hearts float past. The camera tilts down as if sinking with her, catching her eyes open beneath the water before returning to the surface glow.

A pale-skinned woman walks slowly across a shallow silver tide, shattered heart-shaped crystals drifting at her feet. The camera pushes upward from her chest to her eyes as she glances around the endless horizon, then finally fixes her gaze on the lens.

A pale-skinned woman steps through a surreal dreamscape of bending silver trees and melting stars, reaching out as fragments dissolve at her touch. The camera glides forward toward her face as she looks around the shifting world before staring directly into the lens, suspended in unreality.

A pale-skinned woman raises her hand and brushes it across a silver tree trunk, the bark turning to glittering dust beneath her touch. The camera follows her hand upward before locking back onto her eyes, her outline beginning to flicker and dissolve as she whispers silently toward the lens.

A pale-skinned woman sinks slowly beneath violet water, her hand reaching upward as silver light fades. The camera tilts down with her descent, lingering on her face until her eyes close and the surface seals above in absolute stillness.

# 🎬 VRGDG HUMO Music Video Workflow This workflow creates **music videos (or other videos)** in **one shot** using the **HUMO model**. ---
## 1️⃣ HUMO Audio Split **Node:** `VRGDG_LoadAudioSplit_HUMO` - **Input**: URL to the song/audio ⚠️ Use instrumental or lyrics-only - **Outputs**: - `meta` → scene count, timings - `total_duration` → full audio length 💡 `meta` lets `CombineVideos` sync durations automatically. --- ## 2️⃣ Reference Images - Use **one per scene** by default - Swap inputs for **unique images** - Add a **Batch node** for multiple images per scene --- ## 3️⃣ Text-to-Video - Supply images + prompt - HUMO generates a **~3s video segment per scene** --- ## 4️⃣ Combine Videos **Node:** `VRGDG_CombinevideosV2` - Concatenates scenes into a single video - Syncs length from `meta` or durations - Pads shorter clips with last frame - Needs at least **2 video inputs**
## ⚡ Workflow Tips - Chain: **Audio Split → Video Generation → Combine** - `meta` keeps **audio + video in sync** - Clean audio = better results - Use **strong reference images** per scene - Shorter scene lengths keep flow snappy --- ✨ Final Output: **Song + Reference Images + Prompt → Music Video in One Run**

## Set Video Resolution
- Define the **Width** and **Height** for the final video.  
- Keep values **divisible by 16** for best results.  
- Larger sizes = better quality but longer render times.

nodes.title: step 1
widgets_values:
## 🟦 Step 1: Upload Reference Image
- Use **Load Image** to set your main reference.  
- This image will guide the style/look of all scenes.

## 🟦 Step 2: Choose Audio File
- Load your **audio file** into the workflow.  
- ⚠️ Make sure it’s **lyrics-only** (no instruments).  
- The audio will be split into **per-scene snippets** for video generation.

## 🎬 Scene Subgraphs

Each **scene** group is has a **subgraph**.  
Inside the subgraph are the core nodes:  
- `HuMo Embeds` → handles audio + image embeddings  
- `WanVideo Sampler` → generates the video frames  
- `WanVideo Decode` → converts frames back to images  

---

## 🔊 Audio Previews
- Run the workflow until previews update.  
- Cancel, then **listen to the snippet** for that scene.  
- Helps refine prompts so they sync with music.  

---

## ⚡ Editing Each Scene
In each subgraph you only need to adjust:  
- **Text Encoder** → write your per-scene prompt  
- **Reference Image** → optional, only if you want unique images per scene  

Everything else stays pre-wired and ready to go.

## 📦 WAN Models to Download

---

### 🔴 Main HUMO Model  
`WanVideo_comfy_fp8_scaled '

### Whisper Model 
`Whisper Large`  
🔗 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/HuMo/whisper_large_v3_encoder_fp16.safetensors)


---

### 🟣 WAN VAE  
`Wan2_1_VAE_bf16`  
🔗 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/Wan2_1_VAE_bf16.safetensors?download=true)

OR

`wan2_1_vae_fp8`  
🔗 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/calcuis/wan-gguf/resolve/2a7520ea1e79d3f1f3f454a938613235633e1cba/wan2_1_vae_fp8.safetensors)

🗂️ Place in: `ComfyUI/models/vae`


---
### 🟣 WAN Text Encoder
`umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.safetensors`  
🔗 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.safetensors)

OR

`umt5-xxl-enc-fp8.safetensors`  
🔗 [Download Link](https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/umt5-xxl-enc-fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors)

---

🗂️ Place in: `ComfyUI/models/text_encoders`

---

### ⚠️ Torch Compile Warning  
If your setup doesn’t support torch compile, set attention mode to `sdpa` in the model loader, bypass the torch compile node and chang ethe base_precision to fp16

---

### ⚠️ Block Swapping
Block swapping helps with Lower VRAM GPU's and OOM. You can swap up to 40 but it will decrease generation speed. Only use it if you need to.
